ALERT BOX THAT IS SHOWN FOR SOME SECONDS, WHEN SOMETHING IS HAPPENED

Toast CSS Classes
The Toast component is like an alert box that is only shown for a couple of seconds
when something happens (i.e. when the user clicks on a button, submits a form, etc.).

<div class="container">

    <h3>Toast Example</h3>
    <p>A toast is like an alert box that is only shown for a couple of seconds when something happens (i.e. when a user clicks on a button, submits a form, etc.).</p>
    <p>In this example, we use a button to show the toast message.</p>

    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="myBtn">Show Toast</button>

    <div class="toast">

        <div class="toast-header">
            Toast Header
        </div>

        <div class="toast-body">
            Some text inside the toast body
        </div>

    </div>

</div>





